  "prompt": "Can a Permanent Resident get the benefits of paying the tuition fee as a domestic student for doing masters in Australia?",
  "response": "Generally, Permanent Residents (PR) in Australia can get domestic student tuition rates for higher education, including masters programs. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Eligibility Criteria:\n- Must have Australian Permanent Residency status\n- Usually need to have lived in Australia for a certain period\n- Typically must meet residency requirements of the specific university\n\n2. Benefits for Domestic Students:\n- Lower tuition fees compared to international students\n- Eligible for government student loans (HECS-HELP)\n- Access to domestic student scholarships\n\n3. Considerations:\n- Each university might have slightly different specific requirements\n- Some institutions may have additional criteria\n- PR status must be valid at the time of enrollment\n\n4. Documentation Required:\n- Permanent Resident visa\n- Proof of residency\n- Personal identification documents\n\n5. Recommended Steps:\n- Check specific university requirements\n- Contact university admissions directly\n- Confirm exact tuition rates and eligibility\n- Verify loan and scholarship opportunities\n\nWhile PR holders generally qualify for domestic student rates, it's crucial to confirm specific details with individual educational institutions as policies can vary.",
